Idea: Rock that turns into a metal capable of carrying and processing memories. Requires maintenance via Sentience from things like fresh blood, oil, etc. (anything containing DNA). Without maintenance, slowly returns to stone.

Additional Chatty Notes:
Khueenite exists in a semi-living state between mineral and memory-processing medium. When properly maintained with "Sentience" sources such as blood, biological fluids, oils, or other DNA-carrying substances, the material gradually transitions into Sentitanium.

Sentitanium behaves similarly to a biomechanical neural substrate, capable of storing emotional residue, memories, thought-patterns, and even fragments of personality depending on refinement quality.

Without continuous exposure to sentient matter, the material slowly calcifies back into inert stone, effectively "forgetting" accumulated memory structures over time.

Some ancient civilizations used Sentitanium as:
- memory storage
- living circuitry
- emotional archives
- semi-organic processors
- consciousness preservation systems

There are rumors that certain old Sentitanium structures may still contain partially-active personalities trapped within their memory layers.